    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.42-48_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">42</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">
                INTERSTATE HOTEL COMPANY OF NEBRASKA
                LESSEES
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc></figDesc>
                </figure>
                        
                HOTEL FONTENELLE
                
                <hi rend="underline">BUILT FOR YOU TO ENJOY</hi>
                H.EDGAR GREGORY
                MANAGER
                
                <dateline>Apr. 5.</dateline>
                OMAHA, NEB.
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Small print of the hotel building</figDesc>
                    <p>EVERY ROOM WITH A BATH <!--printed as a caption underneath an image of the hotel building--></p>
                </figure>
                 
                    <salute>My dear Friend,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am glad to have made my pilgrimage <del/></p>to <del/> It confims my faith: namely, India is not the only land where <hi rend="underline">Brahmanists</hi> are found. Do you see now that there is no East and West, but the believers in Him and those who don't believe.
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.42-48_0002"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">43</fw>
                
                I hold that we who hold Brahman as the only Reality are a country less, race-less and <hi rend="underline">dressless</hi> lot. Let us mobilise ourselves in and out of India then raise the thought-chant and overcome the Pariahs. The Pariah is in the house <del>in the house</del> of the Lord; the only way we can get rid of him is to raise the vibration in Our Father's mansion to that white heat which will slay all the Pariahs&#8212; they will be simply electrocuted.
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.42-48_0003"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">44</fw>
                        
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">
                        INTERSTATE HOTEL COMPANY OF NEBRASKA
                        LESSEES
                        
                        <figure>
                            <figDesc></figDesc>
                        </figure>
                        
                        HOTEL FONTENELLE
                        
                        <hi rend="underline">BUILT FOR YOU TO ENJOY</hi>
                        H.EDGAR GREGORY
                        MANAGER
                        
                        OMAHA, NEB.
                        
                        <figure>
                            <figDesc>Small print of the hotel building</figDesc>
                            <p>EVERY ROOM WITH A BATH <!--printed as a caption underneath an image of the hotel building--></p>
                        </figure>
                    </hi>
                </fw>
                    
                All over the West I am looking for Hindus like yourself, men who have got the essence of Brahman. Let us meditate each day at a certain hour that 
                <l>Not through bloodshed</l>
                <l>Not by killing</l>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.42-48_0004"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">45</fw>
                
                <l>Not by work</l>
                
                <l>But through love,</l>
                <l>By the Being that burns</l>
                <l>And the Truth that transends</l>
                <l>Time, space, and Eternity</l>
                <l>Brahman shall come,</l>
                <l>For He is here!</l></p>
                
                <p>Pretty unpoetic the above, but it is able to convey the programme and its meaning to any one.</p>
                    
                <p>I really consider you as an
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.42-48_0005"/>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">46</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">
                        INTERSTATE HOTEL COMPANY OF NEBRASKA
                        LESSEES
                        
                        <figure>
                            <figDesc></figDesc>
                        </figure>
                        
                        HOTEL FONTENELLE
                        
                        <hi rend="underline">BUILT FOR YOU TO ENJOY</hi>
                        H.EDGAR GREGORY
                        MANAGER
                        
                        OMAHA, NEB.
                            <figure>
                                <figDesc>Small print of the hotel building</figDesc>
                                <p>EVERY ROOM WITH A BATH <!--printed as a caption underneath an image of the hotel building--></p>
                            </figure>
                    </hi>
                </fw>
                    
                acquisition. I do hope that you will keep in touch with me no matter how remote I be from you.</p>
                
                <figure>unknown characters in sanskrit</figure>
                
                <p>Circumstances but drive the soul to leap out. So you and I
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.42-48_0006"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">47</fw>
                    
                are safe. Our circumstances will be an inducement tho<sic>though</sic> they come as goals to realise Brahman.</p>
                
                <p>I admire your entire family: Four generations of Neihardts. God, what a string!</p>
                
                <p>I love you and your wife. Her spirit is a power.</p> 
                
                <p>Well, as you prey upon Epos by Rythmos remember me as a listener to your singing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Dhau Gopal.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
